After you have configured a project, you can deploy objects from the Source to the Target. After the initial deployment, you can compare objects in the Source and Target to see if any have been updated and need to be deployed again. You can also save objects in the Source to DataPacks.

Deploy Objects from the Source to the Target
When you first create a project, the objects to be deployed still exist only in the source.

Save Objects to a JSON File
Instead of deploying objects to another org, you can save them to a data pack.
